The paper deals with combinatorial quantities and their complexity, which are typical topics in Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves the study of homomorphisms and their relation to counting problems, which are common in Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The paper also uses a theorem to infer a dichotomy, which is a topic in Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper deals with graphs and their structures, which are typical topics in Computational Geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper involves the study of linear combinations, which are common in Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
